<p class="wp-block-paragraph aligncenter has-text-align-center is-style-sub-heading gutenify-section-9f259c10-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 has-primary-500-color has-text-color aligncenter" style="">FAQs</p>

<h2 class="wp-block-heading has-text-align-center gutenify-section-9f265f60-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1" style="margin-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--lg)" id="frequently-asked-questions">Frequently asked questions</h2>

</div>

<div class="wp-block-columns alignwide are-vertically-aligned-top gutenify-section-9f3860c0-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flex wp-container-core-columns-is-layout-8 wp-block-columns-is-layout-flex is-stacked-on-mobile" style="--columns:2" data-columns="2">

<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-top gutenify-section-9f2f8720-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow has-position-relative">

<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default gutenify-section-9f28f770-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow is-style-chevron" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0"><summary style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0;margin-top:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-bottom:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-left:calc(0px - 0)">How do I add custom SVG images?</summary><p class="wp-block-paragraph gutenify-section-9f285b30-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1" style="">Custom SVG images can be added to your site in multiple ways. The first option is to use the core Image block, however this requires the use of the Safe SVG plugin since WordPress doesn&#8217;t allow SVG uploads by default. There is also an SVG block variation provided with this theme which lets you simply paste SVG HTML code into an Image block. The third option is to use the Icon block variation. This displays an SVG icon which you can choose from a library of included icons, or upload your own.</p>

</details>

<details class="wp-block-details gutenify-section-9f2a7e10-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow is-style-chevron" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0"><summary style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0;margin-top:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-bottom:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-left:calc(0px - 0)">How to change the site logo?</summary><p class="wp-block-paragraph gutenify-section-9f29bac0-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1" style="">Head to the Site Editor and then navigate to the Header Template Part. From there, click on the existing logo and then replace it with a block of your choice. You can use an Image block, SVG, Site Logo or Site Title block as the site logo, the choice is yours. We prefer to use SVGs for logos because they scale perfectly at all screen sizes and also support variable colors which makes them ideal for use with dark mode and animations.</p>

</details>

<details class="wp-block-details gutenify-section-9f2c04b0-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow is-style-chevron" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0"><summary style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0;margin-top:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-bottom:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-left:calc(0px - 0)">Does this theme require any plugins?</summary><p class="wp-block-paragraph gutenify-section-9f2b4160-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1" style="">No, there are no plugins required by this theme. Everything you need to design an amazing website is provided by the framework.</p>

</details>

<details class="wp-block-details gutenify-section-9f2d6440-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow is-style-chevron" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0"><summary style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0;margin-top:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-bottom:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-left:calc(0px - 0)">How can I add animations to blocks?</summary><p class="wp-block-paragraph gutenify-section-9f2cc800-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1" style="">Most core blocks have animation supported added. You can add and change transition effects without needing any code.</p>

</details>

<details class="wp-block-details gutenify-section-9f2eeae0-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow is-style-chevron" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0"><summary style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0;margin-top:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-bottom:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-left:calc(0px - 0)">What version of PHP do I need?</summary><p class="wp-block-paragraph gutenify-section-9f2e2790-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1" style="">PHP 7.4 or higher is required however we recommend using a later version PHP 8.2 or above.</p>

</details>

</div>

<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-top gutenify-section-9f379d70-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-column-is-layout-flow has-position-relative">

<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default gutenify-section-9f310dc0-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow is-style-chevron" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0"><summary style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0;margin-top:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-bottom:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-left:calc(0px - 0)">How do I create an FAQ accordion?</summary><p class="wp-block-paragraph gutenify-section-9f304a70-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1" style="">There are 2 ways to add an accordion to your site with our theme. First, you can use an existing accordion from any of the included block patters. Secondly you can create your own from scratch using the core List block. Since the accordion uses a core block variation instead of a custom block, your content will not be lost if you ever decide to switch themes.</p>

</details>

<details class="wp-block-details gutenify-section-9f329460-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow is-style-chevron" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0"><summary style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0;margin-top:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-bottom:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-left:calc(0px - 0)">How can I display blog posts on the home page?</summary><p class="wp-block-paragraph gutenify-section-9f31d110-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1" style="">This theme comes with multiple blog patterns that can be used to display posts on any page. Simply add a blog pattern to your home page template, or the page that is set as the Front Page. You can customize the Query Loop to suit your needs.</p>

</details>

<details class="wp-block-details gutenify-section-9f33f3f0-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow is-style-chevron" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0"><summary style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0;margin-top:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-bottom:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-left:calc(0px - 0)">How can I save user dark mode preferences?</summary><p class="wp-block-paragraph gutenify-section-9f3330a0-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1" style="">No, there are no plugins required by this theme. Everything you need to design an amazing website is provided by the framework.</p>

</details>

</details>

<details class="wp-block-details gutenify-section-9f370130-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1 is-layout-flow wp-block-details-is-layout-flow is-style-chevron" style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0"><summary style="padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs);padding-left:0;margin-top:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-bottom:calc(0px - var(--wp--preset--spacing--xxs));margin-left:calc(0px - 0)">How do I create a child theme?</summary><p class="wp-block-paragraph gutenify-section-9f363de0-01e7-11ef-a9f1-7953640b68a1" style="">We recommend using the create block theme plugin to create your own child themes. With a little know-how, they can be the perfect way to build your own website. They inherit all of the parent theme&#8217;s design which saves you a tonne of work and provides a head start for your next project.</p>

<script id="wp-block-template-skip-link-js-after">

( function() {

var skipLinkTarget = document.querySelector( 'main' ),

sibling,

skipLinkTargetID,

skipLink;

// Early exit if a skip-link target can't be located.

if ( ! skipLinkTarget ) {

return;

}

/*

* Get the site wrapper.

* The skip-link will be injected in the beginning of it.

*/

sibling = document.querySelector( '.wp-site-blocks' );

// Early exit if the root element was not found.

if ( ! sibling ) {

return;

}

// Get the skip-link target's ID, and generate one if it doesn't exist.

skipLinkTargetID = skipLinkTarget.id;

if ( ! skipLinkTargetID ) {

skipLinkTargetID = 'wp--skip-link--target';

skipLinkTarget.id = skipLinkTargetID;

}

// Create the skip link.

skipLink = document.createElement( 'a' );

skipLink.classList.add( 'skip-link', 'screen-reader-text' );

skipLink.href = '#' + skipLinkTargetID;

skipLink.innerHTML = 'Skip to content';

// Inject the skip link.

sibling.parentElement.insertBefore( skipLink, sibling );

}() );

</script>
